1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,000



2
00:00:02,958 --> 00:00:05,541
[female reporter]
Shadyside, small-town America.

3
00:00:06,541 --> 00:00:10,833
But among locals, a history of horror
has earned it another nickname,

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000



5
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,291
"Killer Capital USA."

6
00:00:14,541 --> 00:00:15,375
And last night…

7
00:00:15,458 --> 00:00:17,375
[tires screeching]

8
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:20,250
…tragedy struck again.

9
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:23,875
I'm here with Sheriff Nick Goode.

10
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:26,708
Sheriff, what can you tell us?

11
00:00:26,791 --> 00:00:28,375
Um, there were seven victims.

12
00:00:29,166 --> 00:00:32,291
-[screams]
-[Josh] None of this… is random.

13
00:00:32,375 --> 00:00:33,875
[Deena] Oh my God!

14
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:36,000
[Josh] These massacres
are connected to Sarah Fier.

15
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:39,708
[Josh] 1666,
Sarah Fier was hanged for witchcraft.

16
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:44,208
She's been possessing people,
turning them into killers,

17
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:45,916
to take revenge on the town.

18
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,333
[gunshots]

19
00:00:47,875 --> 00:00:48,833
[tires screeching]

20
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:50,750
[Kate] Go! Go!

21
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:53,583
[menacing music crescendos]

22
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:57,125
But in 1978,
there was one survivor, C. Berman.

23
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:58,333
She's the key.

24
00:01:06,416 --> 00:01:07,458
[Deena] It's over.

25
00:01:08,875 --> 00:01:09,875
[C. Berman] Over?

26
00:01:10,375 --> 00:01:11,500
It's never over.

27
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:13,291
[whispering voice echoes] Sam…

28
00:01:17,416 --> 00:01:19,416
[Deena grunting, screaming]

29
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:21,083
[Sam grunting]

30
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:23,750
[Deena] Get off!

31
00:01:26,583 --> 00:01:28,833
-[grunting]
-[fly buzzing]

32
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:32,166
-I'm going to get you back.
-[roars]

33
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:45,166
[eerie music playing]

34
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:54,916
[female reporter] Killer Capital, USA.

35
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,541
After a week of terror,

36
00:01:56,625 --> 00:01:59,916
Shadyside continues to live up
to its twisted nickname.

37
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,875
Clad in a Halloween skull mask,

38
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:04,208
Shadyside High graduate Ryan Torres

39
00:02:04,291 --> 00:02:07,416
kicked off the days of terror
with a massacre at the mall.

40
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:11,291
And now an already mourning community
is plunged into horror yet again

41
00:02:11,375 --> 00:02:15,083
as the Sheriff's Department reports
more carnage at East Union Medical.

42
00:02:15,166 --> 00:02:18,291
Police believe the murders
were fueled by amphetamines.

43
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:21,791
Local teenagers Kate Schmidt
and Simon Kalivoda

44
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:23,666
are the primary suspects.

45
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:27,250
The scene of the final carnage
was the local grocery store.

46
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:32,250
Sheriff Nick Goode found the Grab and Bag
soaked in blood and broken dreams.

47
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:35,958
[alarm bell ringing]

48
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:44,333
[clocks ticking]

49
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,083
[sighs]

50
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:49,291
["The Man Who Sold The World" playing]

51
00:02:59,166 --> 00:03:01,958
-♪ We passed upon the stair… ♪
-[alarm clock buzzing]

52
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:06,708
-[dog barking]
-♪ We spoke of was and when ♪

53
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:10,875
♪ Although I wasn't there… ♪

54
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:12,375
[dog barking]

55
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:14,791
♪ He said I was his friend… ♪

56
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,250
[dog barking]

57
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:18,250
Major, Jesus!

58
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:20,375
[Major barking]

59
00:03:20,458 --> 00:03:22,166
-[alarm bell ringing]
-[groans]

60
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:23,583
God damn it!

61
00:03:23,666 --> 00:03:26,500
-[music fades out]
-[menacing music playing]

62
00:03:26,583 --> 00:03:27,583
[alarm bell ringing]

63
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:29,458
[Major barking]

64
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:34,166
You're an impatient bastard, aren't you?

65
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:39,833
[man on TV] Sunnyvale is a city of hope.

66
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:44,125
My family have lived here for generations,
cultivating the growth of our city.

67
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,583
And now, as I take the torch

68
00:03:47,208 --> 00:03:49,541
-carried by my forefathers…
-[rapid knocking on door]

69
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:52,750
…I'm ready to bring my experience
to City Hall for another two years.

70
00:03:53,291 --> 00:03:55,625
-[knocking continues]
-I understand the challenges…

71
00:03:55,708 --> 00:03:57,750
[door handle rattling]

72
00:03:57,833 --> 00:04:01,125
[indistinct talk on TV]

73
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:02,583
[Will Goode] I'm here to listen.

74
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:06,833
Let's work together
to keep Sunnyvale shining!

75
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,500
[ominous music playing]

76
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,791
[whispering] It's OK. You stay here.
I'm gonna keep us safe, OK?

77
00:04:16,875 --> 00:04:19,291
[Major whimpering]

78
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:30,375
-[window rattling]
-[breathing heavily]

79
00:04:39,791 --> 00:04:40,833
[woman grunts]

80
00:04:40,916 --> 00:04:43,500
-Don't fucking move!
-[Deena] Wait, wait!

81
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:46,458
Stop, please! Please! We called you.

82
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:49,750
Hello, my name is Deena Johnson.
We need to know how you survived!

83
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:52,541
Hey! We're being attacked, alright?
There are killers here!

84
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,458
-[Deena] Pick up! We need your help!
-[Josh] Please!

85
00:04:55,541 --> 00:04:57,416
[telephone ringing]

86
00:04:58,125 --> 00:04:59,958
-Hello?
-You're still alive.

87
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:02,708
C. Berman…

88
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:03,791
[gasps]

89
00:05:05,416 --> 00:05:06,916
Why the hell would you come here?

90
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:12,916
-[grunting]
-[C. Berman] No!

91
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:17,125
No, no, no! You need to leave! Right now!
You have no idea what you are doing!

92
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,458
[Deena] Wait! Yeah, exactly.

93
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:22,500
You are the only person
who knows what we're dealing with.

94
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:26,458
I don't want that thing near me.
Get that car and "it" off my property.

95
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:27,833
Her name is Sam.

96
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:30,750
You could have watched us dead
on the six o'clock news,

97
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:31,916
but you didn't.

98
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:33,875
You called us back.

99
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:36,541
[sighs] I can't help you with this!

100
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:39,041
You are our last chance! The witch--

101
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,291
No, I'm sorry.

102
00:05:40,375 --> 00:05:44,333
[Deena] My girlfriend is possessed by her
and tied up in a trunk, but you…

103
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:46,666
you saw her and you survived.

104
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:49,333
What was different? Please.

105
00:05:49,416 --> 00:05:53,208
Maybe something happened to you,
something that can help us stop her.

106
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:55,666
[C. Berman] There's not!
You can't stop her.

107
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:59,208
Run, far as you can, fast as you can!

108
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:00,875
That is your only chance.

109
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:03,458
Look, I can't just run!

110
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:05,333
Look, Sam…

111
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,000
I can't let her die.

112
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:10,333
I won't!

113
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,333
I love her.

114
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,583
Please!

115
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:23,625
Just keep her away from Major Tom.

116
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,833
[Sam grunting]

117
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:34,375
[Sam grunting]

118
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,833
[Sam grunting]

119
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,833
[Deena clears throat]

120
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:46,833
It's completely fine.

121
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:50,166
She's tied up in the bathroom,
so she, like,

122
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:52,458
totally can't leave now, we're cool.

123
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:54,000
[Sam roars]

124
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:55,208
[Josh] Yep, cool.

125
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:56,750
Cool, cool.

126
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:02,458
Take a seat.

127
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,041
[clocks ticking]

128
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:10,750
[C. Berman] In Shadyside,

129
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,625
the past is never really past.

130
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:14,166
[breathes shakily]

131
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:21,291
-This was July… 12th.
-[clocks ticking]

132
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:24,166
[C. Berman] The summer of 1978.

133
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:26,333
The first day of camp.

134
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:29,708
[inhales deeply]

135
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:35,875
A week later, my sister was dead.

136
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:40,583
-[ominous music playing]
-[clock chiming]

137
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,833
[girl screams]

138
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:52,875
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit, shit, shit!

139
00:07:52,958 --> 00:07:54,291
[panting]

140
00:07:57,708 --> 00:08:00,166
[dramatic music playing]

141
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,208
[she grunts]

142
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:08,083
[coughing, gasps]

143
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,166
[ravens cawing]

144
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:12,416
[gasping, groans]

145
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,416
You're gonna hang, witch.

146
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,958
[kids chanting]
Before the witch's final breath,

147
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:20,791
she found a way to cheat her death.

148
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:21,875
[redhead] Oh God!

149
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:24,916
[chanting] By cutting off her wicked hand,
she kept her grip upon our land!

150
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,708
She reaches from beyond the grave,
to make good men her evil slaves.

151
00:08:28,791 --> 00:08:32,666
She'll take your blood, take your head,
she'll follow you until you're dead.

152
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:35,083
-[redhead grunts]
-[girl 1] String her up.

153
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,916
[redhead] No, stop it! Stop it! Stop.

154
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,625
[gasps]

155
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:41,666
Let me down, you shits! Let me down!

156
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:50,750
-Well, well. What do we have here?
-Goddamn thief!

157
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,875
[girl 1] No. No, she's no thief.

158
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:55,708
She's possessed by the witch.

159
00:08:55,791 --> 00:08:58,083
The only way to explain
her psycho behavior.

160
00:08:58,166 --> 00:08:59,833
-Fuck you!
-[they gasp]

161
00:08:59,916 --> 00:09:02,291
[redhead panting]

162
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,750
Guess we're even now.

163
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,875
You do know what they did
to Sarah Fier, right?

164
00:09:07,625 --> 00:09:08,791
They hanged her,

165
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:10,833
from this very tree.

166
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:14,583
But she'd have died forever if you did
what you always do to witches…

167
00:09:15,458 --> 00:09:16,541
You burn them.

168
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,500
-Give me your lighter!
-What?

169
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:21,791
Give it to me!

170
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:24,416
Now, hold her legs.

171
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,416
Seriously, Sheila?

172
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,416
Do it! [flicks lighter open]

173
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:31,083
No, no, no! Stop it!
Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

174
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:34,000
-Shut up, you witch.
-Sheila! You made your point.

175
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:36,666
-Don't! Don't!
-[boy] Sheila, it was only ten bucks.

176
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:39,750
[girl 2] Are we really gonna do this?

177
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,583
-Sheila!
-No, no, no!

178
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,875
-[girl 2] Sheila!
-[screams]

179
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,791
-[Sheila] Shit! Will, your brother.
-The hell is this? Let her down!

180
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,041
Nick, I can explain.

181
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:51,000
Let her down, Will!
I swear to God I'll tell Mom!

182
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:53,708
[grunts]

183
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:56,375
[Sheila] I went back to my cabin,
the door was open.

184
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:59,833
All my money was gone
and Ziggy was just sprinting away.

185
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:03,750
-Because you were chasing me.
-Ziggy! You talk when I tell you to talk.

186
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:07,291
-Did you see her take it?
-Everyone did.

187
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:08,833
-[girls] Everyone.
-Alright.

188
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,583
Well, that's it, Berman.
Five strikes. You're out.

189
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:16,458
-I'm out? They just tried to murder me!
-Yeah. And I'll deal with them.

190
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:20,625
But first, get back to camp, call Mommy
because you're done at Nightwing.

191
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:23,250
-I didn't do it.
-[boy 2] Oh, yeah?

192
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,208
Like you didn't set the camp flag on fire?

193
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:28,916
Or let out the camp rabbits?
Or graffiti the outhouse stalls?

194
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:31,041
-I warned you--
-[Sheila] Kurt.

195
00:10:31,125 --> 00:10:33,000
It's not her fault, really.

196
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:37,791
-She's possessed by Sarah Fier.
-Oh, you…

197
00:10:38,416 --> 00:10:40,916
-[Kurt] Hey, hey, hey!
-[Nick] Hey, hey.

198
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:45,125
We kick her out, somebody's gonna ask
about the burn on her arm.

199
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,000
Then who's in trouble? Huh?

200
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:49,583
Why don't we just let this one slide?
Yeah?

201
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:55,666
Alright. One more strike and you're out
for real. You hear me, Berman?

202
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:56,833
One more.

203
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,208
Being bossed around by a Goode.

204
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:03,416
Wow, some things never change.

205
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,458
God, I hate that little bitch.

206
00:11:10,541 --> 00:11:11,958
[children playing, shouting]

207
00:11:12,041 --> 00:11:13,041
[Nick] Hey.

208
00:11:14,958 --> 00:11:18,708
-Have Nurse Lane check that burn out.
-I'm gonna let it get infected and die.

209
00:11:18,791 --> 00:11:20,291
[Nick] I don't get a thank you?

210
00:11:20,375 --> 00:11:21,375
[Ziggy] Oh!

211
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:23,541
I'm sorry, I forgot!

212
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:26,041
Thank you, King of Sunnyvale,

213
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:28,000
future Police Chief Nick Goode,

214
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:31,625
for rescuing poor, helpless Shadysider me!

215
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:33,375
How could I ever repay you?

216
00:11:33,458 --> 00:11:37,166
Oh, I know. I'll bat my eyes at you,
like all the other dumbass girls.

217
00:11:38,166 --> 00:11:42,708
["Brother Love's Traveling Salvation Show"
playing]

218
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:49,083
♪ Hot August night ♪

219
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:54,208
♪ And the leaves hanging down
The grass on the ground smelling sweet ♪

220
00:11:56,791 --> 00:11:59,583
♪ Move up the road… ♪

221
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,500
-Boo!
-[girls scream]

222
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:04,708
♪ And the sound of that good gospel beat ♪

223
00:12:08,375 --> 00:12:10,458
♪ Sits a ragged tent ♪

224
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,000
♪ Where there ain't no trees… ♪

225
00:12:14,083 --> 00:12:18,458
Color War begins tonight, guys! Line up
and grab a shirt! Do you have a shirt?

226
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:21,250
Blue is for beautiful,
if you live in Shadyside.

227
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:23,875
Red is for radiance,
if you live in Sunnyvale.

228
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:26,958
Despite our differences,
we're all perfect!

229
00:12:28,041 --> 00:12:29,791
Even you, Ziggy Berman!

230
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:31,375
♪ And grab the old ladies ♪

231
00:12:31,458 --> 00:12:33,625
♪ And everyone goes ♪

232
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:36,375
♪ 'Cause everyone knows… ♪ [fades out]

233
00:12:36,458 --> 00:12:39,750
["Love Will Keep Us Together"
playing over stereo]

234
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,375
♪ Stop, I'll be thinking of you… ♪

235
00:12:42,458 --> 00:12:44,875
[girl grunting] What is this gunk?

236
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:47,708
It just… It won't come off!

237
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:50,833
That's been there forever, babe.
Just give that up.

238
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:52,958
-Tommy!
-I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

239
00:12:53,041 --> 00:12:56,416
You're right.
It's just, you know, Color War is tonight.

240
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,958
I'm well aware!

241
00:12:58,041 --> 00:13:00,041
We also have to get the Mess Hall ready.

242
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,750
[girl] Oh my gosh.

243
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:05,833
Oh my gosh. This gosh darn moss!

244
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:07,708
It's… it's all over me!

245
00:13:07,791 --> 00:13:11,375
Oh, hey! It's OK! This isn't a big deal.

246
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:14,375
What? No, it's not OK!
It… it… it's stained!

247
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:18,625
Only Cindy Berman would expect
to clean the outhouse and not get dirty.

248
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:20,666
It's not funny!

249
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:22,791
It's kinda funny.

250
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,791
♪ While others pretend ♪

251
00:13:25,875 --> 00:13:29,125
♪ I need you now and I need you then ♪

252
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,500
♪ Just stop… ♪

253
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:32,958
[Cindy gasps] Hey!

254
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:37,333
-What did we talk about?
-[laughing] I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

255
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:39,416
You better be.

256
00:13:39,916 --> 00:13:43,000
♪ Keep us together ♪

257
00:13:43,708 --> 00:13:44,875
♪ Whatever ♪

258
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,875
-[stereo clicks]
-[music stops]

259
00:13:47,458 --> 00:13:48,458
What is it?

260
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,500
[breathing heavily]

261
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:57,291
Where are they?

262
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:58,791
["Cherry Bomb" playing]

263
00:13:58,875 --> 00:14:01,458
[moaning]

264
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,000
[woman groaning] Harder!

265
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:05,458
[both groaning]

266
00:14:06,041 --> 00:14:07,375
[woman] Oh my God!

267
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,500
Oh my… Oh my God!

268
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:11,125
[panting]

269
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:12,125
Hey.

270
00:14:12,208 --> 00:14:14,875
-Um… what are you doing?
-Three guesses.

271
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,208
[man] Hey, careful.

272
00:14:16,291 --> 00:14:18,666
-You don't wanna corrupt her virgin ears.
-[she laughs]

273
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:22,125
[Cindy] We have to get everything together
for Color War. And you guys…

274
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,791
uh, uh… have to finish cleaning
the outhouse.

275
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:29,416
We're doing the shit jobs all summer,
now we have to clean up actual shit? No.

276
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:32,375
-I'm sorry, but we don't have a choice.
-[man] Shit.

277
00:14:34,125 --> 00:14:35,708
This is our last one, babe.

278
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,000
[man flicks lighter]

279
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:40,416
What are you doing?

280
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:42,375
Three guesses.

281
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:43,375
[laughs]

282
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:46,583
-[Cindy groans]
-[music stops]

283
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:48,916
This isn't funny. We have a job to do.

284
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:52,291
-Alice, put that down.
-[Alice] Or what?

285
00:14:52,375 --> 00:14:54,208
What, are you gonna snitch on me again?

286
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:59,500
[chuckles] OK. What if you go talk
to your little friend Nurse Lane.

287
00:14:59,583 --> 00:15:02,500
-About getting us some yellow jackets.
-Yes.

288
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,583
-Or some red birds.
-Both.

289
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:07,708
And then we'll scrub
all the shit you want.

290
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:11,583
-Yellow jackets, red… What?
-Drugs, baby. Drugs.

291
00:15:11,666 --> 00:15:13,083
-Just hook us up.
-[Cindy] No!

292
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:16,208
-No, I won't do that!
-[Alice sighs]

293
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:18,708
Some people want to do things
with their lives.

294
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:22,416
So stop screwing with mine
and just do your jobs, please!

295
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:24,625
Maybe you should have thought about that

296
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:27,958
before blasting Captain and Tennille
for two hours straight.

297
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:31,250
Snitch.

298
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:33,500
[gurgling]

299
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:35,583
[Alice laughs]

300
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:38,541
["Cherry Bomb" continues over stereo]

301
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:39,625
Bye!

302
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:45,250
-[Kurt] Hey!
-[Cindy gasps]

303
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,708
Where have you been?
I've been looking all over.

304
00:15:47,791 --> 00:15:48,833
Your sister…

305
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:51,208
[sniffing]

306
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,208
[sniffing]

307
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:55,500
Cindy Berman, that smell better be skunk.

308
00:15:56,666 --> 00:15:58,000
What about my sister?

309
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,125
[bell ringing]

310
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:02,333
Nurse Lane! Hello!

311
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:05,291
I'm in trouble again. Help.

312
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:09,375
Nurse Lane, come on!
I could die any minute now.

313
00:16:11,541 --> 00:16:14,791
[mysterious music playing]

314
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:16,458
Nurse Lane?

315
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:19,041
Nurse Lane?

316
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:24,041
[mysterious music playing]

317
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:41,916
-[woman] What are you doing?
-Oh my God!

318
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,958
Nurse Lane, you scared the shit out of me.
[inhales deeply]

319
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:48,916
Are you OK?

320
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:50,958
[sighs, sniffs]

321
00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:53,416
I am. Oh my goodness.

322
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,458
Ziggy, Ziggy, Ziggy.

323
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:58,333
What did we do now?

324
00:16:59,166 --> 00:17:04,333
OK, so you are gonna apply this
once a day for three days. OK?

325
00:17:04,416 --> 00:17:06,500
It's gonna protect against infection.

326
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:09,500
It's gross.

327
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:11,750
[scoffs] You'll survive.

328
00:17:15,125 --> 00:17:18,208
So, um… what's the Witch's Mark?

329
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:23,375
[ominous music playing]

330
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:27,250
You know about my daughter, right?
Ruby Lane?

331
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,458
Uh…

332
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,875
-I don't--
-Of course you do.

333
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,583
Everybody talks, I know.

334
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:36,916
Tell me, what do they say?

335
00:17:37,916 --> 00:17:39,833
Uh, um… They say she, uh…

336
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:42,000
she killed people…

337
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,000
at a party.

338
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:46,583
-Seven, seven friends.
-Eight.

339
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:51,000
She killed herself that night too.

340
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:52,333
So eight.

341
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:56,250
Ruby was such a sweet girl.

342
00:17:58,125 --> 00:18:00,916
Oh, and she had a sweet voice.
She was in choir.

343
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,666
She wanted to be a singer.

344
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:06,750
[Ruby singing]
♪ You always hurt the one you love ♪

345
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:08,500
I was so proud of her.

346
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:09,750
So proud.

347
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:14,291
The doctors say
it was a psychotic episode,

348
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:16,250
that she just snapped.

349
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,750
But the kids…

350
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:20,166
the kids say Sarah Fier made her do it.

351
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:22,125
That's a little tight.

352
00:18:22,208 --> 00:18:23,541
-What do you think?
-I don't--

353
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:26,583
'Cause I think you don't go
from being a sweet girl with dreams

354
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:29,333
to ripping someone's insides out
with a switchblade.

355
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:32,291
-Nurse Lane!
-People usually kill for a reason,

356
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:34,416
and sometimes that reason is justified.

357
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,375
Sometimes killing isn't murder.

358
00:18:36,458 --> 00:18:38,875
-Sometimes it's necessary.
-That's hurting me.

359
00:18:38,958 --> 00:18:40,750
-Sometimes it is good.
-Nurse Lane!

360
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,041
Once a day for three days, OK?

361
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:50,083
-[bell ringing]
-[door closes]

362
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:52,416
Hi, Nurse Lane.

363
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:54,541
Hi, Cindy.

364
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:56,000
Ziggy.

365
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:59,875
You realize what happens
if you get kicked out, right?

366
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:03,625
-How awful that would be for me?
-Did someone do something to Nurse Lane?

367
00:19:03,708 --> 00:19:05,541
Like make fun of her daughter?

368
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:08,208
-Ziggy, are you listening to me?
-She was upset.

369
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,458
I don't care! I…

370
00:19:10,375 --> 00:19:13,000
-Do you hear what I'm saying to you?
-Loud and clear, ma'am.

371
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:17,125
You don't, we had this conversation
last week and the week before that.

372
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:20,083
-I'm not gonna get kicked out.
-That's not what Kurt thinks.

373
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:22,791
-Yeah, well, Kurt can suck it.
-No! Ziggy, no!

374
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:24,750
If you get kicked out, I do too.

375
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:29,750
Mom can't work and take care of you.
Then how will I pay for college, huh?

376
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:31,833
-[Ziggy scoffs]
-Oh, that's funny to you?

377
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:33,708
Yeah, kinda.

378
00:19:34,625 --> 00:19:36,708
[chuckles] Explain to me what's so funny.

379
00:19:36,791 --> 00:19:37,916
How dumb you are?

380
00:19:38,416 --> 00:19:41,000
No one gets out of this town,
not even Miss Perfect.

381
00:19:41,083 --> 00:19:43,041
Bet on your way out
you get run over by a bus.

382
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:48,083
Once in your life,
could you just not be so… so mean?

383
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,416
Could once in your life
you just stop pretending?

384
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:54,375
You're Shadyside, in case you forgot.

385
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,791
["Bitterblue" playing]

386
00:19:56,875 --> 00:20:00,333
[Cindy] I swear to God
everyone just wants to ruin my life.

387
00:20:01,291 --> 00:20:03,833
Alice just, like…
She just won't let it go.

388
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:07,458
It's like we're still 12 years old
and her whole goal in life is to…

389
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:09,958
to punish me for something
that wasn't even my fault.

390
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:12,000
I can't believe
you guys used to be friends.

391
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:13,541
And Ziggy… [groans]

392
00:20:14,041 --> 00:20:17,375
It's only a matter of time
before she ends up in jail or worse.

393
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:20,416
I'm trying to be a good role model
and make something of myself.

394
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,041
But no, no,
I'm the stuck-up priss who hates fun,

395
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:25,708
which isn't even true at all.
I like fun. I like fun!

396
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:29,666
I just… I just want
to get out of Shadyside. Is that so crazy?

397
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:32,000
[gasps] Shit!

398
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,250
Shit!

399
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,166
[laughs] Did Cindy Berman just swear?

400
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,708
Not now, Tommy! Not in the mood!

401
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,041
[Cindy sighs]

402
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,041
[sighs] It's OK.

403
00:20:46,041 --> 00:20:47,791
You're OK. You're OK.

404
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:49,125
Just… [inhales deeply]

405
00:20:49,208 --> 00:20:50,083
…breathe.

406
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:52,375
[inhales deeply, sighs]

407
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:00,333
[gasps]

408
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:03,083
[suspenseful music playing]

409
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,500
Tommy, is that you?

410
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:13,791
Tommy?

411
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:16,875
[ominous music playing]

412
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:27,375
[breathing heavily]

413
00:21:28,708 --> 00:21:32,208
["The First Cut Is The Deepest" playing]

414
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,958
Tommy, what are you doing? You're really…

415
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:36,583
♪ …all of my heart… ♪

416
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,041
…freaking me out.

417
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,625
-What is it, babe?
-[Cindy gasps]

418
00:21:43,416 --> 00:21:44,875
[relieved sigh]

419
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:47,000
[gasps]

420
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:49,750
-Nurse Lane?
-[Nurse Lane] I'm sorry.

421
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:50,833
[swallows]

422
00:21:51,916 --> 00:21:53,666
But I can't save you.

423
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:56,000
[suspenseful music playing]

424
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:57,625
[Nurse Lane] I saw your name.

425
00:21:57,708 --> 00:21:59,041
I saw it on the wall.

426
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:00,541
One way or another,

427
00:22:01,208 --> 00:22:02,500
you're gonna die tonight.

428
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:05,083
What are you talking about?

429
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:08,833
-[Nurse Lane screams]
-[Tommy grunts]

430
00:22:09,666 --> 00:22:10,666
[Nurse Lane grunts]

431
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,708
[Cindy gasps]

432
00:22:14,458 --> 00:22:15,750
[Nurse Lane grunts]

433
00:22:18,666 --> 00:22:21,375
♪ …to being lucky, she's cursed ♪

434
00:22:21,458 --> 00:22:23,333
♪ That's how I know ♪

435
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:26,500
♪ The first cut is the deepest ♪

436
00:22:26,583 --> 00:22:28,375
♪ Baby, I know ♪

437
00:22:28,458 --> 00:22:32,666
-♪ The first cut is the deepest ♪
-[gasping]

438
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:38,791
[police officer] You got history with her?
She had a grudge against you?

439
00:22:38,875 --> 00:22:41,291
No grudge. No, we barely ever talked.

440
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:44,166
I… I go to get bug spray from her.
That's it.

441
00:22:44,250 --> 00:22:46,375
It just doesn't…
it doesn't make any sense.

442
00:22:46,875 --> 00:22:49,250
Why… why would she do something like this?

443
00:22:49,916 --> 00:22:53,375
-She was nuts, just like her kid.
-Nurse Lane, she never seemed crazy.

444
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:57,208
That's what she said about her kid, but
sane people don't chop up their friends.

445
00:22:57,791 --> 00:22:59,416
Now, tell me again what happened.

446
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:02,583
[Tommy] Um… uh…
she… she came into the kitchen…

447
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:05,708
Hey, witch. So sorry.

448
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:08,500
I know you and Nurse Psycho were close.

449
00:23:09,083 --> 00:23:11,500
-You can visit her in jail now.
-Fuck off, Sheila.

450
00:23:12,791 --> 00:23:13,958
By the way,

451
00:23:14,041 --> 00:23:16,000
you might want to check your stuff.

452
00:23:16,583 --> 00:23:18,958
I think there was an accident
in cabin five.

453
00:23:19,541 --> 00:23:22,833
[dramatic music playing]

454
00:23:22,916 --> 00:23:25,333
-[girl] Look at her!
-[Sheila] Hurry, witch! Run!

455
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,500
[man 1] Hey, Nicky.

456
00:23:28,083 --> 00:23:29,333
Officer Kapinski.

457
00:23:30,375 --> 00:23:33,708
Been meaning to say I'm sorry
about your Pops. He was a good man.

458
00:23:34,583 --> 00:23:36,833
He was a great man. Taken too soon.

459
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:39,541
Thank you. Yeah. We all miss him.
Big boots to fill.

460
00:23:39,625 --> 00:23:40,458
[chuckles]

461
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:44,041
Well, he was at peace, knowing one day
you'd be following in his footsteps.

462
00:23:44,125 --> 00:23:46,125
Sheriff Nick Goode's got
a good ring to it.

463
00:23:46,208 --> 00:23:49,083
You just go easy on me
when you're my boss, huh?

464
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:53,500
[suspenseful music playing]

465
00:23:53,583 --> 00:23:57,833
[sirens wailing]

466
00:24:00,458 --> 00:24:01,625
[Nurse Lane] I'm sorry.

467
00:24:01,708 --> 00:24:03,041
But I can't save you.

468
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:08,208
One way or another,
you're gonna die tonight.

469
00:24:09,416 --> 00:24:12,708
-[bell ringing]
-[Kurt] Hey, guys! Dinner time!

470
00:24:13,625 --> 00:24:15,541
[man 2] Hey! Hey, come on!

471
00:24:15,625 --> 00:24:19,208
["The Reaper (Don't Fear)" playing]

472
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:22,583
-Nurse Lane's daughter killed 7 people.
-[boy] Her daughter was Ruby Lane.

473
00:24:22,666 --> 00:24:26,500
She was clearly possessed…
just like her crazy daughter.

474
00:24:26,583 --> 00:24:28,125
Sarah Fier strikes again.

475
00:24:28,208 --> 00:24:30,708
-[girl] How does the witch choose them?
-[sighs] It's crazy.

476
00:24:31,208 --> 00:24:33,625
-Is Color War gonna be canceled?
-It starts tonight.

477
00:24:33,708 --> 00:24:36,958
Psycho Shadysiders
always fucking ruin everything!

478
00:24:37,041 --> 00:24:40,000
She said one way or another,
I was gonna die tonight.

479
00:24:40,583 --> 00:24:42,166
Spooky!

480
00:24:42,250 --> 00:24:45,958
The kiddos are right.
That's, like, totally witchy behavior.

481
00:24:46,041 --> 00:24:50,166
It's just, there must be some explanation.
The witch isn't real.

482
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:52,291
-Like what?
-Well, maybe…

483
00:24:55,333 --> 00:24:56,583
Maybe she was on something.

484
00:24:56,666 --> 00:24:59,916
[scoffs] Drugs are peaceful, not violent.

485
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,791
I'm not talking about marijuana.

486
00:25:02,875 --> 00:25:07,750
Just admit you're jealous that the witch
wanted your hubby all to herself!

487
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:11,375
Be serious, man. Why would Nurse Mary
wanna do something like that?

488
00:25:11,458 --> 00:25:14,500
-Why would she want me dead?
-Oh, no. She wouldn't.

489
00:25:15,083 --> 00:25:16,625
[both] But the witch might!

490
00:25:16,708 --> 00:25:18,208
[girl laughing]

491
00:25:18,291 --> 00:25:20,708
Hey, they're just playing around.

492
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,000
This was nothing, I promise.

493
00:25:23,083 --> 00:25:24,416
Did you see her eyes?

494
00:25:25,375 --> 00:25:28,083
There was something in there,
something wrong.

495
00:25:30,583 --> 00:25:33,500
-[loud clapping]
-[shouting] Alright!

496
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,166
-[cheering]
-Chicks, dicks, listen up!

497
00:25:36,250 --> 00:25:39,708
We had a scary situation earlier,
but we cannot let that mess

498
00:25:40,208 --> 00:25:43,041
with the most important night
of our summer.

499
00:25:44,083 --> 00:25:47,833
Tonight is Sunnyvale versus Shadyside.

500
00:25:47,916 --> 00:25:51,583
It is red versus blue.
It is good versus evil.

501
00:25:52,416 --> 00:25:56,166
Tonight, we commencicate Color War!

502
00:25:56,250 --> 00:25:59,041
-[cheering]
-It's "commence." My god.

503
00:25:59,125 --> 00:26:03,166
He might be dumb,
but he's kind of shagadelic.

504
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:06,375
-Oh yeah!
-He's disgusting. You're disgusting.

505
00:26:06,458 --> 00:26:10,541
Tonight's first event
is Capture the Flag, baby.

506
00:26:10,625 --> 00:26:13,125
-[cheering]
-Yeah, yeah, yeah! Now, Sunnyvalers…

507
00:26:13,708 --> 00:26:16,041
[whispering] We have never, ever…

508
00:26:17,083 --> 00:26:18,625
[shouting] …lost a Color War!

509
00:26:18,708 --> 00:26:20,333
[cheering, chanting] Sunnyvale!

510
00:26:20,416 --> 00:26:22,208
So let's not let tonight

511
00:26:22,291 --> 00:26:24,625
be a stain on our legacy.

512
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:26,208
[chanting] Sunnyvale!

513
00:26:26,291 --> 00:26:27,416
[Kurt] And let's go out there

514
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:31,958
like our ancestors before us

515
00:26:32,041 --> 00:26:36,041
and murder those Shadyside witches!

516
00:26:36,125 --> 00:26:38,250
-[crowd] Yeah!
-[Kurt laughs] Woo!

517
00:26:38,333 --> 00:26:39,916
[cheering]

518
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,000
[cheering]

519
00:26:41,083 --> 00:26:42,333
Uh, hi! [giggles]

520
00:26:43,083 --> 00:26:45,625
Thank you, Kurt, for that neat-o speech.

521
00:26:46,375 --> 00:26:48,750
Now, Shadysiders,

522
00:26:49,458 --> 00:26:53,250
let's go out there and do our best,

523
00:26:53,333 --> 00:26:55,416
because even if we lose,

524
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:59,250
we're still winners in our hearts.

525
00:26:59,333 --> 00:27:00,750
Boo!

526
00:27:00,833 --> 00:27:02,041
[Kurt] Boo!

527
00:27:02,125 --> 00:27:03,750
[booing]

528
00:27:03,833 --> 00:27:06,583
[chanting] Sunnyvale! Sunnyvale!

529
00:27:06,666 --> 00:27:09,583
["Moonage Daydream" playing]
♪ I'm an alligator ♪

530
00:27:09,666 --> 00:27:12,583
♪ I'm a mama-papa comin' for you ♪

531
00:27:13,291 --> 00:27:15,333
♪ I'm the space invader… ♪

532
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:16,833
What are you doing?

533
00:27:17,958 --> 00:27:19,125
Art project.

534
00:27:19,208 --> 00:27:21,500
-I need to talk to you.
-I'm not in the mood.

535
00:27:21,583 --> 00:27:23,875
Earlier, you said Mary was upset.

536
00:27:23,958 --> 00:27:26,875
-[scoffs] Oh, so now you care!
-Ziggy, this is serious.

537
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:29,583
It was serious earlier,
and you didn't give a shit.

538
00:27:32,208 --> 00:27:35,583
Come on, you were the last person
to see her before she snapped.

539
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:38,625
What about drugs? Did you see any around?

540
00:27:39,208 --> 00:27:40,833
She's a nurse, so yup.

541
00:27:40,916 --> 00:27:43,750
-Well, did she mention anything or--
-Nope.

542
00:27:43,833 --> 00:27:46,958
Ziggy, I'm just… I'm trying to understand
what happened today.

543
00:27:47,041 --> 00:27:49,000
[Ziggy] Who cares? It's over.

544
00:27:49,083 --> 00:27:53,583
[Cindy] Not for Tommy. He's still
freaked out and acting weird and…

545
00:27:53,666 --> 00:27:57,125
It's just a big joke to everyone.
"Mary was possessed by the witch."

546
00:27:57,208 --> 00:27:59,083
-Maybe it was the witch.
-Ziggy…

547
00:27:59,166 --> 00:28:02,875
What? That doesn't fit your carefully
constructed bullshit view of the world?

548
00:28:02,958 --> 00:28:04,750
-Why are you being like this?
-I dunno.

549
00:28:04,833 --> 00:28:07,333
Maybe because Nurse Lane was
the only person who was nice to me,

550
00:28:07,416 --> 00:28:11,208
and now her life is over because
bad things always happen to Shadysiders.

551
00:28:11,291 --> 00:28:13,541
Nothing just happens.
There's always a reason.

552
00:28:13,625 --> 00:28:17,000
Not always a rational one.
Deep down, you feel it, don't you?

553
00:28:17,083 --> 00:28:21,708
Shadyside, there's something here.
It's just holding us down, cursing us.

554
00:28:21,791 --> 00:28:24,375
-Ziggy, that's enough.
-You're too scared to admit it.

555
00:28:24,875 --> 00:28:27,166
When things go bad,
you wanna explain it away.

556
00:28:27,250 --> 00:28:31,041
I'm sorry. I'm not going to blame
everything on some fairy tale.

557
00:28:31,125 --> 00:28:35,041
Life sucks sometimes. I get that.
I mean, God knows it's been hard since…

558
00:28:35,125 --> 00:28:36,458
Since what?

559
00:28:36,541 --> 00:28:38,416
See, you can't even say it!

560
00:28:38,500 --> 00:28:39,958
Since Dad left.

561
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:41,875
Since Mom started drinking.

562
00:28:41,958 --> 00:28:43,791
Since we're going to lose the house.

563
00:28:43,875 --> 00:28:45,875
And it's not gonna magically get better.

564
00:28:46,458 --> 00:28:51,541
And saving up all summer to buy
a super cute polo shirt can't hide that.

565
00:28:52,625 --> 00:28:57,583
Trying to explain why nice old Nurse Lane
almost lost it today can't either.

566
00:28:57,666 --> 00:28:59,083
We're all cursed.

567
00:28:59,875 --> 00:29:01,250
For Mary, it was today.

568
00:29:02,208 --> 00:29:04,416
But someday, it'll be you.

569
00:29:04,500 --> 00:29:07,416
And this whole fake
bullshit life of yours,

570
00:29:07,500 --> 00:29:09,500
it's gonna come crashing down.

571
00:29:09,583 --> 00:29:11,583
That's a horrible thing to say.

572
00:29:12,375 --> 00:29:13,833
It's not horrible if it's true.

573
00:29:15,583 --> 00:29:17,958
I don't know who you are anymore, but…

574
00:29:19,625 --> 00:29:20,916
But you're not my sister.

575
00:29:21,875 --> 00:29:22,791
Then who am I?

576
00:29:23,458 --> 00:29:24,458
A monster.

577
00:29:25,375 --> 00:29:27,708
[ominous music playing]

578
00:29:29,541 --> 00:29:30,791
That's what they say.

579
00:29:43,916 --> 00:29:47,958
["Carry On Wayward Son"
playing over loudspeaker]

580
00:29:48,041 --> 00:29:50,833
♪ There'll be peace when you are done ♪

581
00:29:52,125 --> 00:29:56,083
♪ Lay your weary head to rest ♪

582
00:29:56,166 --> 00:29:58,416
♪ Don't you cry no more… ♪

583
00:29:59,333 --> 00:30:04,541
Do… do not let them anywhere near this.
Do you hear me?

584
00:30:04,625 --> 00:30:05,666
[all shouting] Yeah!

585
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:08,333
[Kurt] I said, do you hear me?

586
00:30:08,416 --> 00:30:09,833
[all] Yeah!

587
00:30:11,041 --> 00:30:12,666
[laughter]

588
00:30:12,750 --> 00:30:14,458
[chanting] Shadyside! Shadyside!

589
00:30:14,541 --> 00:30:16,041
[whooping]

590
00:30:16,125 --> 00:30:17,875
[Tommy] Alright, alright, alright!

591
00:30:17,958 --> 00:30:21,916
Now remember, keep at least
three defenders by this all the time.

592
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,625
Alright? And who's the jailer?

593
00:30:23,708 --> 00:30:27,666
OK, Jeremy, you may be
the most important player in the, uh…

594
00:30:29,166 --> 00:30:30,208
in the…

595
00:30:30,708 --> 00:30:31,708
[groans]

596
00:30:34,083 --> 00:30:36,500
[whispering voice echoes] Tommy…

597
00:30:36,583 --> 00:30:38,791
-[Cindy] Tommy!
-[chanting] Sunnyvale!

598
00:30:38,875 --> 00:30:40,875
-Sunnyvale!
-Are you OK?

599
00:30:40,958 --> 00:30:42,500
Yeah, are you OK, Mr. Slater?

600
00:30:43,458 --> 00:30:45,500
Yeah, I'm… I'm good. Um…

601
00:30:45,583 --> 00:30:47,750
Why don't you guys get started?
Plant the flag.

602
00:30:47,833 --> 00:30:51,500
And I'll be right behind you. OK?
Let's go, Shadyside! Come on!

603
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:52,833
[chanting] Shadyside! Shadyside!

604
00:30:52,916 --> 00:30:54,125
Move, move, move!

605
00:30:54,208 --> 00:30:55,250
Oh, man.

606
00:30:56,333 --> 00:30:59,541
My head is throbbing.
She must have got me pretty good.

607
00:31:00,125 --> 00:31:03,291
-Mary's stronger than she looks.
-You need to lie down?

608
00:31:03,375 --> 00:31:06,125
No. No, I'm alright. I'm alright.

609
00:31:06,208 --> 00:31:07,666
Good. I need your help,

610
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:09,958
and the key to the infirmary.

611
00:31:10,791 --> 00:31:14,250
[suspenseful music playing]

612
00:31:20,125 --> 00:31:22,375
[fire crackling]

613
00:31:30,125 --> 00:31:31,708
[door creaks]

614
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,083
[Tommy] So, what exactly
are we looking for?

615
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:40,916
Answers.

616
00:31:41,750 --> 00:31:44,083
Come on, Cindy.
It doesn't matter, alright?

617
00:31:44,166 --> 00:31:45,625
It matters.

618
00:31:45,708 --> 00:31:48,500
There's a reason Mary did what she did
and said what she said.

619
00:31:48,583 --> 00:31:51,666
-We're going to figure it out now.
-Come on, Cindy. Please, I…

620
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:52,958
[Tommy sighs]

621
00:31:54,291 --> 00:31:55,291
[sighs]

622
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,208
[chuckles]

623
00:32:04,291 --> 00:32:05,791
No label, half-empty.

624
00:32:06,666 --> 00:32:08,500
Like I said, she was on drugs.

625
00:32:09,791 --> 00:32:12,416
Get these to the cops,
then they'll tell us what they…

626
00:32:13,875 --> 00:32:14,916
What is that?

627
00:32:15,416 --> 00:32:17,708
"A deal was made with the Devil."

628
00:32:18,875 --> 00:32:21,041
"Sarah Fier cut off her wicked hand

629
00:32:21,125 --> 00:32:24,791
on Satan's stone
in exchange for eternal life,

630
00:32:25,500 --> 00:32:28,500
scarring the soil beneath
with the witch's mark,

631
00:32:29,458 --> 00:32:31,416
bringing Darkness upon the land."

632
00:32:33,333 --> 00:32:34,708
[glass breaks]

633
00:32:37,208 --> 00:32:38,416
Did you hear that?

634
00:32:40,916 --> 00:32:43,208
[menacing music playing]

635
00:32:46,291 --> 00:32:49,583
[floorboards creaking]

636
00:32:49,666 --> 00:32:50,666
[Tommy] Hello?

637
00:32:52,625 --> 00:32:54,291
Hello, is somebody in there?

638
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:58,916
-Argh!
-Jeez!

639
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:01,333
-[Alice laughing]
-Come on. That's not funny.

640
00:33:02,166 --> 00:33:04,791
Alice? What are you doing here?

641
00:33:04,875 --> 00:33:07,625
[scoffs] Looks like we're both here
for the same thing.

642
00:33:09,250 --> 00:33:11,291
Must really want me
to scrub those toilets.

643
00:33:11,375 --> 00:33:12,666
This isn't for you.

644
00:33:12,750 --> 00:33:15,833
Whoa, Berman. I didn't know
you were into that kind of thing.

645
00:33:15,916 --> 00:33:19,000
They're not for me.
I'm giving them to the cops.

646
00:33:19,083 --> 00:33:20,250
Oh yeah, the cops.

647
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:22,250
Yeah, right, of course.

648
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:26,541
No, what are you talking about?
What, now you're gonna snitch on Mary too?

649
00:33:27,125 --> 00:33:28,750
No. That's… I'm trying to--

650
00:33:28,833 --> 00:33:31,125
-This for the cops too?
-Give that back!

651
00:33:31,208 --> 00:33:32,875
[Alice laughing]

652
00:33:33,708 --> 00:33:36,375
[spooky voice]
"She emerged by the Meeting House,

653
00:33:36,458 --> 00:33:39,833
one hand severed, lost forever."

654
00:33:39,916 --> 00:33:41,791
"We hanged the witch,

655
00:33:41,875 --> 00:33:43,500
body chained and buried

656
00:33:43,583 --> 00:33:45,041
but without her hand,

657
00:33:45,583 --> 00:33:48,791
her grip on the land holds firm."

658
00:33:48,875 --> 00:33:50,166
Ooh! [laughing]

659
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:52,500
This is Sarah Fier shit!

660
00:33:52,583 --> 00:33:54,708
Alice, come on.

661
00:33:54,791 --> 00:33:57,125
"When she is near, blood will fall

662
00:33:57,791 --> 00:34:02,250
and the curse will last
until body and hand unite."

663
00:34:02,333 --> 00:34:05,291
Alice, it's Mary's diary.
Let's put it back.

664
00:34:05,875 --> 00:34:07,000
It's not just a diary.

665
00:34:09,875 --> 00:34:10,958
It's a map.

666
00:34:11,541 --> 00:34:12,500
What?

667
00:34:12,583 --> 00:34:15,416
Crazy Nurse Lane made a crazy map.

668
00:34:19,250 --> 00:34:22,250
It's camp,
but looks like she drew all over it.

669
00:34:23,833 --> 00:34:26,208
1666 Union.

670
00:34:26,291 --> 00:34:28,416
-Union, that's Shadyside.
-What?

671
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:31,875
The settlement before it was divided
into Shadyside and Sunnyvale.

672
00:34:31,958 --> 00:34:34,041
-Really?
-If you went to class…

673
00:34:34,125 --> 00:34:37,208
So, the camp is built in the same place
as the settlement?

674
00:34:38,541 --> 00:34:40,750
Whoa, look, look, look! Sarah Fier!

675
00:34:40,833 --> 00:34:43,916
-Do you think that's her house?
-[man] What are all the X's?

676
00:34:44,750 --> 00:34:46,416
There's only one way to find out.

677
00:34:48,291 --> 00:34:49,583
Hey! That's my bag!

678
00:34:49,666 --> 00:34:50,666
Arnie, flashlight.

679
00:34:51,333 --> 00:34:53,416
[Alice laughing]

680
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:55,375
-What is this shit?
-Let me see.

681
00:34:55,458 --> 00:34:57,041
[kids playing, laughing]

682
00:34:57,958 --> 00:34:59,041
L484.

683
00:35:00,208 --> 00:35:03,166
-Sounds familiar. Ooh, Dex, maybe.
-Know what sounds fun?

684
00:35:04,041 --> 00:35:06,708
-Seeing a witch's house high on Dex.
-Oh yes, it does.

685
00:35:06,791 --> 00:35:10,458
Alice! Bring that back!
What are you doing?

686
00:35:10,541 --> 00:35:14,083
It's called fun, Cindy Berman.
You used to have it, remember?

687
00:35:14,166 --> 00:35:16,791
-[Alice] We're gonna find you, Sarah Fier!
-Tommy! [echoing]

688
00:35:17,625 --> 00:35:20,208
[whispering voice] Tommy…

689
00:35:20,291 --> 00:35:21,458
[Cindy] Tommy!

690
00:35:21,541 --> 00:35:23,541
Come on, they took everything!

691
00:35:24,250 --> 00:35:26,958
["Ever Fallen In Love" playing]

692
00:35:33,333 --> 00:35:34,666
[knocking on door]

693
00:35:34,750 --> 00:35:35,916
Go away, Cindy!

694
00:35:36,458 --> 00:35:37,875
It's me. It's Nick.

695
00:35:39,541 --> 00:35:40,875
Go away, Nick!

696
00:35:42,541 --> 00:35:43,375
Whoa.

697
00:35:45,166 --> 00:35:47,833
-I like what you've done with the place.
-This wasn't me.

698
00:35:47,916 --> 00:35:48,916
[Nick] I'm shocked.

699
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:51,583
"Ziggy is a witch bitch."

700
00:35:51,666 --> 00:35:54,875
"Ziggy sucks cocks in Hell." Jeez.

701
00:35:56,166 --> 00:35:57,083
Sheila?

702
00:35:57,708 --> 00:35:58,625
Colonel Mustard.

703
00:36:00,541 --> 00:36:04,250
-Oh, looks like blood.
-Yeah. I didn't have a pig, so…

704
00:36:05,458 --> 00:36:06,458
Carrie. Cool.

705
00:36:08,375 --> 00:36:09,375
You've read Carrie?

706
00:36:09,458 --> 00:36:11,916
Yeah. Second favorite after Salem's Lot.

707
00:36:12,583 --> 00:36:13,625
[Ziggy chuckles]

708
00:36:13,708 --> 00:36:16,833
Still, I dunno,
paint seems a little pedestrian.

709
00:36:16,916 --> 00:36:18,916
Oh, I'm sorry. Do you have a better idea?

710
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,416
Maybe.

711
00:36:20,500 --> 00:36:22,875
Shouldn't you be, like,
turning me in or something?

712
00:36:22,958 --> 00:36:26,541
Well, I should be supervising
Color War, uh…

713
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:31,333
-But noticed you were MIA and--
-So you decided to stalk me.

714
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,166
Check in on you.

715
00:36:33,750 --> 00:36:37,208
Clearly you don't need my assistance.
All good. Go ahead.

716
00:36:37,291 --> 00:36:38,375
"Carrie" on.

717
00:36:42,833 --> 00:36:43,875
What's your idea?

718
00:36:44,916 --> 00:36:46,000
[keys jingling]

719
00:36:47,583 --> 00:36:48,541
Science & Nature.

720
00:36:50,541 --> 00:36:51,625
[Cindy] Alice!

721
00:36:52,541 --> 00:36:53,541
Alice!

722
00:36:54,166 --> 00:36:57,000
Come on, it's disgusting in here!

723
00:36:57,083 --> 00:36:59,791
[Alice] We're close,
Berman, hang in there!

724
00:37:01,125 --> 00:37:03,125
This was the best idea.

725
00:37:04,125 --> 00:37:06,166
Yeah, but I still don't feel shit.

726
00:37:06,875 --> 00:37:08,708
OK, so, take more.

727
00:37:09,416 --> 00:37:10,416
Thank you.

728
00:37:12,083 --> 00:37:13,083
L484.

729
00:37:13,833 --> 00:37:15,458
-[Alice] Arnie!
-[Arnie] Wait up!

730
00:37:15,541 --> 00:37:16,541
[Cindy] Alice!

731
00:37:17,791 --> 00:37:19,916
I swear to God… [gasps]

732
00:37:21,625 --> 00:37:22,541
Shit!

733
00:37:22,625 --> 00:37:25,000
-Oh, it's ruined now!
-You cursed again.

734
00:37:26,291 --> 00:37:27,833
You want me to murder you?

735
00:37:28,583 --> 00:37:29,958
-Babe, you OK?
-[Tommy] Yeah.

736
00:37:30,041 --> 00:37:31,875
Yeah, I'm fine. [sniffs]

737
00:37:31,958 --> 00:37:33,083
[Alice screams]

738
00:37:33,958 --> 00:37:35,000
[Cindy] Alice?

739
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:38,875
[suspenseful music playing]

740
00:37:47,666 --> 00:37:48,583
Watch your step.

741
00:37:51,083 --> 00:37:52,833
[Tommy] Is someone digging a grave?

742
00:37:54,250 --> 00:37:55,375
[Alice] Graves.

743
00:38:00,291 --> 00:38:01,375
Mary.

744
00:38:02,666 --> 00:38:03,875
Hey, where's the, uh…

745
00:38:05,791 --> 00:38:07,500
The X's, look. Look.

746
00:38:11,250 --> 00:38:13,583
Look, here. Here.

747
00:38:13,666 --> 00:38:15,166
She was marking where she dug.

748
00:38:18,250 --> 00:38:19,791
[Alice] "But without her hand,

