1048
00:53:37,791 --> 00:53:38,958
Why do you care?

1049
00:53:39,041 --> 00:53:40,083
I'm curious.

1050
00:53:41,666 --> 00:53:44,666
-I've hated her since I was a baby. Next.
-[Nick] Come on.

1051
00:53:45,250 --> 00:53:47,875
Why are you so full of shit?

1052
00:53:47,958 --> 00:53:49,000
[scoffs] What?

1053
00:53:49,083 --> 00:53:50,208
Nick Goode,

1054
00:53:50,750 --> 00:53:52,000
heir apparent,

1055
00:53:52,875 --> 00:53:55,125
Daddy was the police chief,
the King of Sunnyvale,

1056
00:53:55,208 --> 00:53:56,375
you're gonna be the same.

1057
00:53:56,458 --> 00:53:58,083
Except it's all make-believe.

1058
00:53:59,458 --> 00:54:04,166
The truth is you like Stephen King
and spiders and…

1059
00:54:05,458 --> 00:54:07,291
the weird girl from Shadyside.

1060
00:54:07,791 --> 00:54:08,958
Alright, first of all,

1061
00:54:09,625 --> 00:54:12,666
Stephen King is, like, super popular.

1062
00:54:13,250 --> 00:54:14,333
And, second,

1063
00:54:15,833 --> 00:54:17,375
I can't like the weird girl.

1064
00:54:17,458 --> 00:54:18,750
Why not?

1065
00:54:19,541 --> 00:54:21,000
Because I'm a counselor.

1066
00:54:21,083 --> 00:54:22,333
She's a camper.

1067
00:54:22,416 --> 00:54:24,458
Last year for me. First year for you.

1068
00:54:24,541 --> 00:54:29,833
Plus, how will I ever get to know her
when she keeps dodging my questions?

1069
00:54:41,458 --> 00:54:44,000
There was a time
when things were good between us.

1070
00:54:44,083 --> 00:54:47,333
When my dad was around
and my mom was happy,

1071
00:54:47,416 --> 00:54:49,208
and my sister and me, we would, um…

1072
00:54:50,416 --> 00:54:52,625
we'd throw toilet paper
on Mr. Corkle's tree,

1073
00:54:52,708 --> 00:54:55,375
and then go jump in the lake
in all our clothes and…

1074
00:54:57,375 --> 00:54:58,458
And now…

1075
00:55:00,250 --> 00:55:02,791
Now it's just gone and everything's shit.

1076
00:55:05,416 --> 00:55:07,541
That's what happens
when you live in Shadyside.

1077
00:55:08,041 --> 00:55:10,083
Everything turns to shit eventually.

1078
00:55:10,166 --> 00:55:13,416
[sentimental music playing]

1079
